Tom Emerson wrote:

&gt; I have a stored profile that I use for all of my crawls that contains
&gt; the elaborate (well, that may be an overstatement, but I do tweak a
&gt; lot of nobs and add filters and such) settings used. How well does the
&gt; current HEAD deal with being handed an order file that may not be
&gt; up-to-date with it&#39;s current settings?
&gt;
&gt; In other words, is there a clean upgrading path, or should I just
&gt; recreate the profile from scratch?

I tried it.  There was one issue where an old default didn&#39;t make the 
transition nicely so I added code to handle this in HEAD.  Otherwise, 
there is one manual change that needs to be made because a parameter 
changed type from &#39;string&#39; to &#39;stringList&#39;.  Here is the edit you need 
to make:

+++ order.xml   2005-02-01 13:12:34.000000000 -0800
@@ -162,7 +162,9 @@
         &lt;string name=&quot;prefix&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/string&gt;
         &lt;string name=&quot;suffix&quot;&gt;&lt;/string&gt;
         &lt;integer name=&quot;max-size-bytes&quot;&gt;100000000&lt;/integer&gt;
-        &lt;string name=&quot;path&quot;&gt;arcs&lt;/string&gt;
+        &lt;stringList name=&quot;path&quot;&gt;
+          &lt;string&gt;arcs&lt;/string&gt;
+        &lt;/stringList&gt;
         &lt;integer name=&quot;pool-max-active&quot;&gt;5&lt;/integer&gt;
         &lt;integer name=&quot;pool-max-wait&quot;&gt;300000&lt;/integer&gt;
       &lt;/newObject&gt;

Otherwise, should just work (I&#39;ve added a note on upgrading old profiles 
and order files to release notes).

